INTERNET VIDEO CONTENT AS A SUSTAINABLE TOOL FOR MARKETING

By Ebubechukwu Henrietta Umeobi

ABSTRACT
¶

Across decades, data through videos have been used to analyze people’s behavior, watch their spending habits and lifestyle and in a lot of cases, influence their decision making. Videos play a huge role in influencing marketing strategies across all industries and so the question remains: one can have a good product/solution, but how will it be sold through the internet?

RESEARCH QUESTIONS
¶

My research questions are:

  1. Which categor(ies) of videos are viewed the most on YouTube in the selected countries?
  2. Which days have the highest trends in the selected countries?
  3. Which categor(ies) of videos were viewed the most prior to the COVID-19 pandemic in the selected countries?
  4. Which country has the highest number of user engagement on YouTube (likes, dislikes, comments)?
  5. What are the popular video tags?

DATA¶

Using YouTube data, I'm curious to know what people are interested in watching. I chose this because internet content creation, especially video content, is simply one of the most interesting concepts of the 21st century. I retrieved my dataset from Kaggle’s YouTube videos updated live data here. For this final project, my focus will be on these selected countries: Russia, United States of America, Japan, Denmark, United Kingdom, France, Mexico, Canada and India. This is for the purpose of making inductive generalisations for the Western, South Asian and subcontinental Indian population. Other Asian and African population were avoided due to the complexities of cultures and diversity of languages found in the populace as culture and language have great impact on content creation, thus, generalisations cannot be quickly made in settings as diverse as the African populace as well as the entirety of Asia.

TOOLS AND GUIDELINES¶

  • The project will be executed using Python on Google Colaboratory interface and Jupyter Notebook.
  • In loading of the dataset, the pandas Python environment will be used. This environment is a fast, powerful, flexible and easy to use open source data analysis and manipulation tool,built on top of the Python programming language
  • Pandasql and SQLite will also be used for observing results by creating a database of the selected countries for ease of analysis.
  • Graphical analysis of the project will be done using some analytics graphics tools such as Seaborn, Plotly Express and MatPlot Library
  • For the pupose of verification across other programming languages which specifically analyse my type of database, Tableau Desktop will be used.

ISO = []

for i in yt["Country"]:
    if i == "USA":
        ISO.append("USA")
    elif i == "CANADA":
        ISO.append("CAN")
    elif i == "UK":
        ISO.append("GBR")
    elif i == "FRANCE":
        ISO.append("FRA")
    elif i == "DENMARK":
        ISO.append("DNK")
    elif i == "INDIA":
        ISO.append("IND")
    elif i == "JAPAN":
        ISO.append("JPN")
    elif i == "SOUTH KOREA":
        ISO.append("KOR")
    elif i == "MEXICO":
        ISO.append("MEX")
    elif i == "RUSSIA":
        ISO.append("RUS")
    else:
        ISO.append("")
yt["ISO"] = ISO

from datetime import datetime 

def changedate_formate(yt):
  split = yt.split('.')
  a = split[1]
  b = split[2]
  c = split[0]
  ''.join(a+b+c)
  return

SUMMARY¶

The analyses given in the above graphs show that the highest views on YouTube are in the Music category, followed by Film & Animation and Gaming categories. Between the time frame of the data (2017 to June 2018), the highest viewing trend was in February 2018 in the People and Blogs category. Generally, prior to the announcement of SARS COVID-19 pandemic, the TOP 5 most viewed video categories were: Music, Gaming, Film & Animation, Comedy and People's & Blogs. The LOWEST 5 viewed categories in the selected countries were (in no order): Education, NonProfits & Activism, News & Politics, Pets & Animals and Travels & Events.

However, using Tableau queries, the top viewed categories in the selected countries was and still is: Music, Entertainment, Film & Animation and Gaming. This poses a theory that viewers in these selected countries watched the same categories regardless of the prevalence of the COVID-19 pandemic.

CONCLUSION¶

YouTube has been in existence since 2005 as a website for sharing videos. If the vision of the founders included people using video content creation as a way of making more income than newspapers, we might never know. But this almost 30 billion dollar company (statista, 2022), which makes more than 100 million dollars revenue from advertising daily by the first quarter of 2021 (Music Busines Worldwide, 2022), has majority of its views from the Music industry in our analysis.
